Insert into Summary (`BookID`,`Summary`) Values ('1470','We find that the APC can processively ubiquitinate target substrates, transferring multiple ubiquitin molecules to the substrate during a single binding event. The efficiency of this reaction depends upon the APC subunit Doc1; APC that are lacking only Doc1 display significant defects in the processivity of substrate ubiquitination. Biochemical analysis indicates that Doc1 stimulates processivity by enhancing the affinity of the substrate-APC interaction. Importantly, the interaction of Cdh1 with the APC is not affected by Doc1, suggesting that Doc1 contributes to the binding of substrates to core APC subunits.') ;
